    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1b: \"In primary hippocampal neurons derived from wild-type rat, CIN85 (SH3KBP) is localized to dendritic spines, in which it is accumulated in post-synaptic compartments, co-localizing with F-actin and PSD-95 (DLG4), closely juxtaposing the pre-synaptic synaptophysin protein\"\n\nFigure 1c: \"CIN85 (SH3KBP) localizes to actin-positive, spine-like structures in dendrites of primary rat striatal neurons. Cells were fixed and stained with antibodies against CIN85 (SH3KBP) and with rhodamine phalloidin\"\n\nFigure 1d,e: \"biochemical fractions showed CIN85 (SH3KBP) was enriched in PSD fractions together with marker protein PSD95 (DLG4).\"\n\nFigure 4: \"CIN85 co-clusters with D2 dopamine receptors (D2DRs) at punctuate synapse-like structures in primary rat striatal neurons\"\n\nFigure 5: \"CIN85 co-immunoprecipitates with D2DRs, the endocytic proteins endophilin and dynamin, as well as the post-synaptic density protein PSD-95, in wild type, but not in CIN85Δex2 knockout samples\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"In primary hippocampal neurons derived from wild-type rat, CIN85 (SETA antibody, green) is localized to dendritic spines\"",
